properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 10 at 8:55PM EST until January 11 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southeast winds 20 to 25 knots increasing to 25 to 30
knots prior to sunrise. Wind gusts 35 to 40 knots from the early
morning through afternoon. Winds will begin to decrease after
sunset on Saturday. Seas initially 5 to 8 feet will build to 9
to 12 feet with occasional seas up to 14 feet well offshore.

* WHERE...From Okaloosa/Walton County line to Apalachicola out to
60 nautical miles, as well as from Apalachicola to the Suwannee
River Entrance between 20 and 60 nautical miles from shore.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
